        The system determines whether a version is old or new. This information is not presented to users. The value of the version-code tag is an integer greater than 0. A larger value indicates a newer version. This tag must be specified. You must have configured it in the configuration file.

      • getReqPermissions

        public List<String> getReqPermissions​()
        Obtains the required permissions applied for by the application.

        The permissions are derived from the values of name in the reqPermissions attribute of the config.json file.

        Before calling this method, you must have obtained the bundle information by passing the IBundleManager#GET_BUNDLE_WITH_REQUESTED_PERMISSION flag to the IBundleManager#getBundleInfo(String, int) method.

        Returns:
        Returns the list of required permissions applied for by the application.
        Since:
        3
